findings.ims:
There is a misconfiguration in the I-CSCF's Diameter XML configuration file, `/etc/kamailio_icscf/icscf.xml`. While the I-CSCF has an open Diameter connection to the HSS, its Location-Information-Requests (LIRs) are timing out, causing call failure. The S-CSCF uses a similar configuration file and communicates successfully with the same HSS, proving the HSS is functional. The fault therefore lies in an application-level parameter within the I-CSCF's XML file, such as an incorrect Application-ID or Vendor-ID for the Cx interface, which causes the HSS to drop the requests. My tools cannot read this specific XML file, so I cannot pinpoint the exact parameter.

**raw_evidence_context:**
```
// I-CSCF config pointing to external XML
156:modparam("cdp","config_file","/etc/kamailio_icscf/icscf.xml")

// S-CSCF config pointing to external XML
243:modparam("cdp","config_file","/etc/kamailio_scscf/scscf.xml")

// Triage metric showing I-CSCF timeouts
ims_icscf:uar_timeouts = 1.0

// E2E trace showing I-CSCF failure reason
SIP/2.0 500 Server error on LIR select next S-CSCF
```
